{
  "stem": "17761.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I was not in a concentration camp, but in a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We left the-- the train left the city the evening of Hoshana Rabbah or the-- and in that train, there were around 1,000, 900 Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were in wagons for cattle, pressed together, youngsters, older people, sick people, healthy people, you name it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father became immediately quite the commander of this wagon.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Every wagon had an elder.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Romanian army, they were responsible for this train.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had the right to open up a little place to have some air.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This they let us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember in the morning, we came [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] at a train station, a central train station called Darmanesti, D-A-R-M-A-N-E-S-T-I.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And suddenly, the train stopped in the field.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my father says to me, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Look.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There is a tree with hoshanot.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I jumped out of the train and broke up a branch of it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I run back and the train started to move.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My father caught me up back to the-- to the wagon.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so under these conditions, we had the Sefer Torah and we had a hoshanot.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You cannot imagine.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "My father had one prayer book.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Not everybody had prayer books.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "People wanted to just to kiss the Torah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was something unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And so the train went through Bukovina into Bessarabia and brought us to a place called Atachi, A, double T, A-C-H-I, which is at the border of the Dniester.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "There was a terrible mud because of the rains and because the Dniester flooded up.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "There was a flood.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And that year, there was a lot of rains in that year.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And you don't know what the [NON-ENGLISH] mud is.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "You just get drowned there.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
